The article discusses President Obama's visit to the L'Aquila earthquake zone in Italy with Prime Minister Berlusconi. The President expressed sympathy and solidarity with the earthquake victims and the people of Italy. The United States is providing support to the Abruzzo region through a public-private partnership with the National Italian-American Foundation (NIAF). This support includes scholarships for University of L'Aquila students to attend U.S. universities while the damaged university is rebuilt, as well as modular buildings to house students and university facilities. The U.S. State Department is also assisting with summer sports camps, educational exchange opportunities, and donations of reference materials to libraries and archives in L'Aquila. The goal of these projects is to help the University of L'Aquila return to its previous academic, social, and economic role in the region.